In fiscal 2023, we worked with TANSAM, the Tamilnadu Smart and Advanced Manufacturing Centre, to build and equip an incubation center in India to spur industrial inno- vation at the grassroot level. The center employs under- privileged people and has already trained more than 16,000 students on Industry 4.0 skills.

Access to technology on the basis of our core competencies We want to share our knowledge about automation, digita-

lization, and intelligent infrastructure with the intention of making it accessible to people around the world.